article.headline: Albany, N.Y. 63, Cent. Connecticut St. 60
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Jon Iati scored 15 points that including a key 3-pointer late in overtime Wednesday to lead Albany to a 63-60 win over Central Connecticut, spoiling the Blue Devils' home opener. Iati hit the 3 with 2:03 left to give the Great Danes (1-1) a 63-59 lead. Shemik Thompson hit a free throw in the final minute to pull the Blue Devils within three. Central (0-2) had its chances with time running out, but Tristan Blackwood's shot from the right corner with seven seconds left fell short. Thompson and Blackwood each scored 12 points for Central Connecticut. Blackwood had seven rebounds for the Blue Devils to go along with four assists. Blackwood got the Blue Devils to overtime. Central trailed 58-56 in regulation until Blackwood hit a layup with 16.2 seconds left to tie it. The game was tied four times in the first half until Albany went on an 8-2 run that featured a pair of buckets by Tim Ambrose. The Great Danes led 36-28 at the break after shooting nearly 54 percent from the floor.
